      • unlock

        boolean unlock(KeyPair[] keyPairs)
        Unlocks the GpsControl object to be used at the given web address.
        More than one set of path-key pairs my be passed in.
        See documentation site for more info on getting a key.
        Parameters:
        keyPairs - array of KeyPair
        Returns:
        whether unlock was successful
        Since:
        Minimum plugin version 2.0.0.4

      • startFindDevices

        void startFindDevices()
        Initiates a find GPS devices action on the plugin.
        Poll with finishFindDevices() to determine when the plugin has completed this action.
        Use getDevicesXml() to inspect XML contents for and array of Device nodes.
        Since:
        2.0.0.4

      • cancelFindDevices

        void cancelFindDevices()
        Cancel the current find devices interaction.
        Since:
        2.0.0.4

      • finishFindDevices

        boolean finishFindDevices()
        Get state of last find devices action
        Returns:
        true if completed finding devices otherwise false.
        Since:
        2.0.0.4

      • getDevicesXml

        String getDevicesXml()
        Returns information about the number of devices connected to this machine as well as the names of those devices. Refer to the Devices element in the GarminPluginAPIV1 schema for what is included. The XML returned should contain a 'Device' element with 'DisplayName' and 'Number' if there is a device actually connected.
        Returns:
        XML, potentially empty if no devices found

      • getDevices

        Device[] getDevices()
        Parses getDevicesXml() values into a Device array
        Returns:
        empty array if no devices found
